If you don't have a #toaster{}, preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7 for the
naans. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, add the garlic, @diced British chicken breast{1%pack}, @chermoula
spice mix{1/2%sachet}, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @Zhoug style paste{1%tbsp}
and @Greek Style natural yoghurt{1%tbsp} (add less if you prefer things milder). Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Mix to coat the chicken in the zhoug yoghurt.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

== Rocket & Tomato Salad ==

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{1}(cut into 1cm chunks).

In a medium bowl, combine the tomato, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the yoghurt-coated chicken to the pan.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and
season with @salt and @pepper if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Zhoug Yoghurt ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the remaining @Zhoug style paste{1/2%tbsp} and
@Greek Style natural yoghurt{1%tbsp}.

== To Serve ==

Cut the @plain naans{2} in half widthways, then put in your toaster until golden. If
you're using the oven, put the naans onto a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with a little
@water{} and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the tomato bowl. Toss to coat.

When everything's ready, share the toasted naans between your plates.

Top with the chermoula chicken and the rocket and tomato salad.

Drizzle over the zhoug yoghurt to finish. Enjoy!